WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:20.479
It feels cheap to call it a friendship.

3
00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:25.752
It was something else. Like a kinship.

4
00:00:25.776 --> 00:00:27.903
From deep in our souls.

5
00:00:29.321 --> 00:00:32.382
We could face anything that
life would throw in our paths

6
00:00:32.406 --> 00:00:35.160
as long as we had each
other to come back to.

7
00:00:37.287 --> 00:00:39.748
We were supposed to grow old together.

8
00:00:40.999 --> 00:00:44.294
What we had was… it was powerful.

9
00:00:45.462 --> 00:00:47.172
and essential.

10
00:00:48.382 --> 00:00:52.177
and it was supposed to last forever.

11
00:00:57.349 --> 00:00:59.017
But that's not what happened.

12
00:01:55.407 --> 00:01:57.659
When was the last time
you saw the deceased?

13
00:01:58.535 --> 00:02:00.454
We had dinner last night?

14
00:02:01.079 --> 00:02:02.664
You don't seem sure about that.

15
00:02:03.415 --> 00:02:06.376
No. I am. I'm sorry. I am. I just…

16
00:02:07.628 --> 00:02:10.672
It doesn't seem possible
that that was yesterday.

17
00:02:11.173 --> 00:02:15.010
You know. everything
feels… just so different now.

18
00:02:19.556 --> 00:02:21.016
Can I ask how?

19
00:02:23.727 --> 00:02:25.455
What happened?

20
00:02:25.479 --> 00:02:26.813
Was she robbed?

21
00:02:27.856 --> 00:02:29.525
Was she raped?

22
00:02:30.526 --> 00:02:33.195
That's not information
we can share just now.

23
00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:35.715
We're hoping you can help us.

24
00:02:35.739 --> 00:02:37.425
Yes. However I can.

25
00:02:37.449 --> 00:02:39.219
What… what can I do?

26
00:02:39.243 --> 00:02:43.306
You may have been the last person to
talk to your friend before the assailant.

27
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:47.417
so you can tell us anything that
you remember from last night.

28
00:02:56.677 --> 00:02:58.738
Okay. okay. okay. okay.

29
00:02:58.762 --> 00:02:59.763
Here we go.

30
00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:07.896
Let's go! Thank you.
thank you. thank you.

31
00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:13.443
I would like to thank my coworkers on
the south Asian team for letting me win.

32
00:03:16.405 --> 00:03:19.342
And I have to thank our
fearless leader. Eleanor.

33
00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:22.554
for the two most rewarding.
challenging years of my life.

34
00:03:22.578 --> 00:03:24.806
- May I say something?
- Of course.

35
00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:25.831
So…

36
00:03:26.415 --> 00:03:32.897
These somewhat ridiculous
cornhole contests do serve a purpose.

37
00:03:32.921 --> 00:03:35.775
And it's not just to
bring some joy and levity

38
00:03:35.799 --> 00:03:38.778
to the really difficult but crucial work

39
00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:40.905
that all of you are
doing all over the world.

40
00:03:40.929 --> 00:03:44.016
These moments also
Mark passageways.

41
00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:48.788
So. kumal. we raise our
compostable cups to you today

42
00:03:48.812 --> 00:03:52.458
because we are so proud of
everything that you have accomplished

43
00:03:52.482 --> 00:03:53.751
at rescue and relief.

44
00:03:53.775 --> 00:03:57.547
And we are even more proud
of all the work on your horizon.

45
00:03:57.571 --> 00:03:59.340
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

46
00:03:59.364 --> 00:04:00.842
To kumal!

47
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:02.177
Everyone. please eat!

48
00:04:02.201 --> 00:04:03.952
I don't wanna waste any food.

49
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:10.417
Thank you.

50
00:04:12.669 --> 00:04:14.731
- Good speech. boss.
- What?

51
00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:16.483
I was just. you know.
giving you a compliment.

52
00:04:16.507 --> 00:04:17.507
Don't do that.

53
00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:21.571
- What's up?
- Do you have a second to talk?

54
00:04:21.595 --> 00:04:23.615
I don't. I'm… I'm so sorry. I don't.

55
00:04:23.639 --> 00:04:26.058
- But maybe we can find some time later?
- Yeah.

56
00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:29.478
Yeah? I'll see you later? Okay.

57
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:36.568
I'm watching.

58
00:04:37.694 --> 00:04:40.715
Wait. Do I… I know…
do I have to do this?

59
00:04:40.739 --> 00:04:42.091
- You do.
- It's tradition.

60
00:04:42.115 --> 00:04:43.760
- Yes.
- From college.

61
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:45.845
When we were young
and we had bad taste.

62
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:48.765
- El. help me.
- I'm… I do not make the rules.

63
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:51.333
- Happy to be here. Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

64
00:04:54.503 --> 00:04:55.563
God. no.

65
00:04:55.587 --> 00:04:56.898
It's gotten worse.

66
00:04:56.922 --> 00:04:57.982
- Yeah.
- Disgusting.

67
00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:59.067
It's really bad.

68
00:04:59.091 --> 00:05:03.196
Okay. honey. how has the day been?
Have you been adequately worshipped?

69
00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:07.033
Absolutely. Artemis woke up at
6:00 A.M. to start worshipping me.

70
00:05:07.057 --> 00:05:09.244
By demanding pancakes.

71
00:05:09.268 --> 00:05:13.164
No. they were so sweet. the girls. and
Howard had them write me little poems.

72
00:05:13.188 --> 00:05:14.499
- That is sweet.
- Yeah. I know.

73
00:05:14.523 --> 00:05:16.042
It's kinda cheap.

74
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:17.794
- It's personal.
- Nancy.

75
00:05:17.818 --> 00:05:20.213
She deserves to be showered with gifts.

76
00:05:20.237 --> 00:05:21.673
Excuse me.

77
00:05:21.697 --> 00:05:24.300
Potato mini-galettes with tomato con fit.

78
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:26.469
Paired with champagne.
Compliments of the chef.

79
00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:28.513
Thank you. Please thank Marco for me.

80
00:05:28.537 --> 00:05:29.597
Will do. Ms. Bouchet.

81
00:05:29.621 --> 00:05:31.057
Thank you.

82
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:32.141
Amazing.

83
00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:33.560
Very nice.

84
00:05:33.584 --> 00:05:35.061
I mean. they're tater tots. right?

85
00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:39.274
No. they are very
fancy. artisanal tater tots.

86
00:05:39.298 --> 00:05:40.692
Don't be rude.

87
00:05:40.716 --> 00:05:42.527
I love it when you sleep with chefs.

88
00:05:42.551 --> 00:05:44.279
How's it going with the coworker?

89
00:05:44.303 --> 00:05:48.324
Is that still… yes. we are still connecting.

90
00:05:48.348 --> 00:05:50.910
- Here and there. You know?
- Yeah.

91
00:05:50.934 --> 00:05:52.203
It's very casual though.

92
00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:53.746
- Does he know that?
- Yes.

93
00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:55.772
- Nancy. you good?
- Fantastic.

94
00:05:56.773 --> 00:05:58.418
- What?
- Is everything okay?

95
00:05:58.442 --> 00:05:59.919
Yes!

96
00:05:59.943 --> 00:06:02.463
Ladies. I wanted to say that...

97
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:04.465
is this gonna be long?
'Cause I have to pee.

98
00:06:04.489 --> 00:06:05.884
- No.
- Okay. I'm just checking.

99
00:06:05.908 --> 00:06:09.929
I just wanted… I wanted to say that I'm
so happy to be here with the two people

100
00:06:09.953 --> 00:06:12.640
that I love most. who I feel
most loved by in the whole world.

101
00:06:12.664 --> 00:06:13.850
- Wow. Sweetheart!
- We do love you.

102
00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:15.185
There's an Irish saying that…

103
00:06:15.209 --> 00:06:17.979
- God. Please don't.
- I'm just kidding.

104
00:06:18.003 --> 00:06:19.439
- Go.
- Happy birthday. baby.

105
00:06:19.463 --> 00:06:20.923
Thank you.

106
00:06:21.798 --> 00:06:23.467
All right. I'll be right back.

107
00:06:25.677 --> 00:06:28.764
- We have your table ready. Ms. Bouchet.
- Fantastic. Thank you.

108
00:06:31.934 --> 00:06:34.496
Nancy. what is going on? Are you okay?

109
00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:35.771
Yeah. No…

110
00:06:37.064 --> 00:06:38.583
- What's happening?
- It's that guy.

111
00:06:38.607 --> 00:06:41.169
It's still happening.

112
00:06:41.193 --> 00:06:42.670
- I know.
- What?

113
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:44.464
I thought you were
breaking it off with him.

114
00:06:44.488 --> 00:06:46.508
I tried. I know. It's complicated.

115
00:06:46.532 --> 00:06:47.634
What does that mean?

116
00:06:47.658 --> 00:06:49.385
Mary doesn't know.

117
00:06:49.409 --> 00:06:51.387
Can you not say anything? I…

118
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:53.247
I don't wanna make her upset.

119
00:06:54.414 --> 00:06:56.250
But it's okay for me to be upset?

120
00:06:57.668 --> 00:07:00.104
Well. it's not like you're monogamous.

121
00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:05.693
Nancy. if you were being honest
with Robert about what you were doing.

122
00:07:05.717 --> 00:07:06.986
that would be fine.

123
00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:08.988
I mean. open marriages are
like open kitchens these days.

124
00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:12.408
- Everybody's putting 'em in.
- It's not exactly Robert's style.

125
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:17.497
But this thing that you are
doing. it's not liberating you.

126
00:07:17.521 --> 00:07:21.108
- It's just making you miserable.
- I know. I know. I…

127
00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:26.613
It's just when I'm with
him. I feel powerless.

128
00:07:29.867 --> 00:07:31.469
Do you remember what you said to me

129
00:07:31.493 --> 00:07:35.289
about the difference
between love and infatuation?

130
00:07:36.748 --> 00:07:37.916
What did I say?

131
00:07:38.584 --> 00:07:43.439
You said that love fills you up
and infatuation depletes you.

132
00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:44.691
Are you sure I said that?

133
00:07:44.715 --> 00:07:46.067
- Yes.
- That sounds more like Mary.

134
00:07:46.091 --> 00:07:48.319
No. you said it to me. About Robert.

135
00:07:48.343 --> 00:07:50.554
The day that he proposed.

136
00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:55.618
Sometimes I think you see
my life more clearly than I do.

137
00:07:55.642 --> 00:07:59.914
- No. I just…
- hi! The view is beautiful. - Hi!

138
00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:00.999
Right?

139
00:08:01.023 --> 00:08:02.316
What are we talking about?

140
00:08:03.567 --> 00:08:06.528
Just Eleanor's entanglements.

141
00:08:07.196 --> 00:08:10.675
Well… I was offered
cocaine in the bathroom.

142
00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:12.010
What?

143
00:08:12.034 --> 00:08:14.053
I didn't take it. but. you
know. it's nice to be asked.

144
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:15.138
You still got it!

145
00:08:15.162 --> 00:08:16.246
Thank you.

146
00:08:34.681 --> 00:08:37.327
- Hey.
- Eleanor. it's Robert.

147
00:08:37.351 --> 00:08:40.288
Sorry to bother you so late or so early.

148
00:08:40.312 --> 00:08:41.914
It's okay. What's up?

149
00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:43.625
Well. Nancy didn't come home last night.

150
00:08:43.649 --> 00:08:45.335
and she's not answering her phone.

151
00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:48.070
She didn't go home with you
after dinner by any chance?

152
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:50.989
Are you there?

153
00:08:51.532 --> 00:08:55.094
- You okay?
- Yeah… I'm… I'm sorry. Are you not alone?

154
00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:56.328
No. no…

155
00:08:56.912 --> 00:08:59.331
Can you just give me a second?

156
00:09:08.131 --> 00:09:09.591
Okay. so…

157
00:09:11.134 --> 00:09:12.821
Nancy hasn't come home yet?

158
00:09:12.845 --> 00:09:15.448
No. and I've left half a
dozen messages and texts.

159
00:09:15.472 --> 00:09:16.866
There's no response.

160
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:18.284
Very concerning.

161
00:09:18.308 --> 00:09:20.912
Yeah. I don't… I don't know. Robert.

162
00:09:20.936 --> 00:09:24.398
I mean. we ate and then she left.

163
00:09:25.107 --> 00:09:26.650
And she told you she was coming home?

164
00:09:28.402 --> 00:09:31.280
I mean. she didn't say
that exactly. but I assumed…

165
00:09:34.449 --> 00:09:35.969
That's it. I'm calling the police.

166
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:40.247
- No. Robert. Don't… don't do that.
- Okay. so…

167
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:42.934
What. you do know where she is?

168
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:44.936
Not exactly.

169
00:09:44.960 --> 00:09:46.962
Eleanor. what the hell's going on?

170
00:09:50.007 --> 00:09:52.485
I'm gonna throw some
clothes on and come to you.

171
00:09:52.509 --> 00:09:53.778
That's not necessary.

172
00:09:53.802 --> 00:09:55.071
If you could just tell me w...

173
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:59.308
Robert. stop! Stop. Do not call the
police until we talk. okay? Please.

174
00:10:00.142 --> 00:10:02.203
- Okay. okay.
- Okay.

175
00:10:02.227 --> 00:10:03.663
I'm on my way.

176
00:10:03.687 --> 00:10:05.314
Shit!

177
00:10:07.733 --> 00:10:08.734
Hey. Jordan.

178
00:10:10.819 --> 00:10:11.987
Can I take these jeans?

179
00:10:13.030 --> 00:10:14.573
- Yeah.
- Okay.

180
00:10:15.365 --> 00:10:17.468
You leaving already?

181
00:10:17.492 --> 00:10:22.539
Yeah. but it's fine 'cause I
was never here. remember?

182
00:11:19.888 --> 00:11:20.973
Hey.

183
00:11:22.766 --> 00:11:24.351
So. she's done with me?

184
00:11:25.936 --> 00:11:27.271
She's leaving?

185
00:11:27.938 --> 00:11:29.040
Is that what this is?

186
00:11:29.064 --> 00:11:33.086
I don't know what she's
thinking. and she hasn't said that.

187
00:11:33.110 --> 00:11:34.337
What? Jesus. Eleanor.

188
00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:36.506
Come on. you came all the way over
here. You might as well just tell me.

189
00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:37.739
Is she seeing someone else?

190
00:11:40.742 --> 00:11:41.910
I'm so sorry.

191
00:11:45.914 --> 00:11:47.207
Well…

192
00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:49.644
There it is.

193
00:11:49.668 --> 00:11:51.920
I really don't wanna be
in the middle of all this.

194
00:11:54.673 --> 00:11:55.883
So. who is he?

195
00:11:56.425 --> 00:11:58.987
She told me it was over. But
you know how Nancy is. right?

196
00:11:59.011 --> 00:12:00.989
Like. sometimes she's very
clear. and then another...

197
00:12:01.013 --> 00:12:02.055
I need a name.

198
00:12:04.850 --> 00:12:06.161
- David.
- David who?

199
00:12:06.185 --> 00:12:07.227
I don't know.

200
00:12:07.895 --> 00:12:09.956
She says that she met him through work.

201
00:12:09.980 --> 00:12:12.584
The museum? The ballet? Hospital?

202
00:12:12.608 --> 00:12:14.210
Where… where did she find this guy?

203
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.694
She hasn't told me.

204
00:12:18.822 --> 00:12:24.220
So. this dinner with you and Mary
last night. that's. what. her alibi?

205
00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:27.223
No. We had dinner. We were
celebrating Mary's birthday.

206
00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:28.749
Don't lie to me.

207
00:12:29.333 --> 00:12:30.435
Been lied to enough.

208
00:12:30.459 --> 00:12:31.460
Not by me.

209
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:34.939
I have never lied to you. Not once.

210
00:12:34.963 --> 00:12:38.967
We all had dinner. and then she left.

211
00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:42.596
Would you like a drink?

212
00:12:43.472 --> 00:12:45.098
- I quit.
- What?

213
00:12:46.225 --> 00:12:47.327
When?

214
00:12:47.351 --> 00:12:49.037
Two weeks ago.

215
00:12:49.061 --> 00:12:50.687
Feels like a year.

216
00:12:51.855 --> 00:12:53.315
I did it for her.

217
00:12:57.986 --> 00:12:59.321
Is this new?

218
00:12:59.863 --> 00:13:00.924
I don't know.

219
00:13:00.948 --> 00:13:03.510
She's always moving the art
around. Says it keeps things fresh.

220
00:13:03.534 --> 00:13:05.845
Is she really that unhappy with me?

221
00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:09.265
I know she shares everything
with you and Mary. but…

222
00:13:09.289 --> 00:13:10.666
Don't do that. Robert.

223
00:13:11.875 --> 00:13:16.213
It's not you. She is unhappy with herself.

224
00:13:19.633 --> 00:13:23.470
Thanks for coming by. but I.
I need to get myself together.

225
00:13:38.110 --> 00:13:40.171
Can we ask you to sit. sir?

226
00:13:40.195 --> 00:13:42.948
I'd rather stand.

227
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:48.680
A body was found early this morning that
we have reason to believe is your wife's.

228
00:13:48.704 --> 00:13:49.872
Nancy's.

229
00:13:53.834 --> 00:13:55.711
How do you know it was her?

230
00:13:56.253 --> 00:13:59.065
A wallet containing her
identification was found with the body.

231
00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:00.483
God.

232
00:14:00.507 --> 00:14:01.717
Yeah. well…

233
00:14:04.928 --> 00:14:05.929
Where?

234
00:14:06.555 --> 00:14:07.890
In arroyo seco park. sir.

235
00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:11.536
Under the Colorado street bridge.
there's a walkway there and...

236
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:13.812
I know the arroyo. I've lived
in Pasadena my whole life.

237
00:14:14.438 --> 00:14:16.148
What happened to her?

238
00:14:17.191 --> 00:14:20.402
The evidence suggests there
was an assault that killed her.

239
00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:24.161
And unfortunately those are all
the details we can tell you right now.

240
00:14:28.994 --> 00:14:31.914
We will need someone from
the family to identify the body.

241
00:14:36.001 --> 00:14:37.920
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

242
00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:40.547
What did you just say?

243
00:14:41.465 --> 00:14:43.550
We need someone to identify the body.

244
00:15:08.742 --> 00:15:11.221
Yes. That's her.

245
00:15:11.245 --> 00:15:12.538
That's…

246
00:15:15.165 --> 00:15:16.416
That's Nancy.

247
00:15:22.881 --> 00:15:24.132
Ms. Bouchet.

248
00:15:25.843 --> 00:15:27.135
Ms. Bouchet!

249
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:30.889
I asked how long you and the
deceased had known one another.

250
00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:36.663
We've been best friends
for 25 years with Mary.

251
00:15:36.687 --> 00:15:40.917
Look. I… I have to call Mary
because she can't read about this.

252
00:15:40.941 --> 00:15:44.403
You told Mr. Hennessey that
she was seeing another man.

253
00:15:45.112 --> 00:15:46.339
Yes.

254
00:15:46.363 --> 00:15:47.781
What do you know about him?

255
00:15:48.907 --> 00:15:49.968
Not a lot.

256
00:15:49.992 --> 00:15:52.077
His name is David.

257
00:15:53.412 --> 00:15:55.056
They met at work.

258
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:56.516
- At work?
- Yes.

259
00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:59.602
Mr. Hennessey tells us
she was a homemaker.

260
00:15:59.626 --> 00:16:02.438
Yes. She does a lot
of philanthropic work.

261
00:16:02.462 --> 00:16:05.942
She sits on the board of
several different organizations.

262
00:16:05.966 --> 00:16:08.236
I'm sure that Robert could
give you a complete list.

263
00:16:08.260 --> 00:16:10.512
We're talking to you right now.

264
00:16:11.638 --> 00:16:15.267
Is there anything more that
you can tell us about her lover?

265
00:16:15.934 --> 00:16:19.831
Hair color? Age? Race? Height?

266
00:16:19.855 --> 00:16:21.833
- Weight?
- No. I'm sorry.

267
00:16:21.857 --> 00:16:23.751
I wish there were.

268
00:16:23.775 --> 00:16:26.153
My wife has a best friend from college.

269
00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:28.705
Can't get 'em off the
phone with each other.

270
00:16:30.574 --> 00:16:31.867
Is that a question?

271
00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:37.164
Just seems she might have
told you more than a first name.

272
00:16:39.082 --> 00:16:40.334
Well. she didn't.

273
00:16:41.043 --> 00:16:42.628
As it happens.

274
00:16:47.758 --> 00:16:49.736
Am I being held?

275
00:16:49.760 --> 00:16:51.738
Or am I free to go?

276
00:16:51.762 --> 00:16:53.573
Somewhere else you need to be?

277
00:16:53.597 --> 00:16:55.408
You are free to go.

278
00:16:55.432 --> 00:16:57.309
Just do us a favor and stay in town.

279
00:16:59.728 --> 00:17:01.080
Of course.

280
00:17:01.104 --> 00:17:02.231
Thank you.

281
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:29.383
No problem.

282
00:17:31.593 --> 00:17:33.303
What's so funny about that?

283
00:17:34.263 --> 00:17:35.681
Hi! Hey!

284
00:17:36.723 --> 00:17:38.743
- Aunt Ellie!
- Hi.

285
00:17:38.767 --> 00:17:39.869
I got a cut on my toe.

286
00:17:39.893 --> 00:17:41.079
- It's infected.
- Whoa!

287
00:17:41.103 --> 00:17:42.163
I got a cat!

288
00:17:42.187 --> 00:17:43.540
- You did?
- She started feeding a cat.

289
00:17:43.564 --> 00:17:44.999
- It's not hers.
- Yes. it is!

290
00:17:45.023 --> 00:17:46.209
- No. it's not.
- Yes. it is!

291
00:17:46.233 --> 00:17:48.086
Stop lying. you liar! Mom.
tell her it's not her cat!

292
00:17:48.110 --> 00:17:50.797
This is a nice surprise. Are you okay?

293
00:17:50.821 --> 00:17:53.174
- No. it's not. No. you don't.
- Yes. I do!

294
00:17:53.198 --> 00:17:54.968
Sweetie. will you take
them inside for a second?

295
00:17:54.992 --> 00:17:56.845
Hey. come on. girls. Who
wants some iPad time?

296
00:17:56.869 --> 00:17:57.971
- Go on.
- iPad!

297
00:17:57.995 --> 00:18:00.497
Ellie and mommy need
some. grown-up time.

298
00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:04.668
What is it?

299
00:18:08.213 --> 00:18:09.298
It's Nancy.

300
00:18:11.758 --> 00:18:12.759
What?

301
00:18:13.302 --> 00:18:15.721
- Mary.
- What?

302
00:18:17.931 --> 00:18:19.016
She's gone.

303
00:18:19.850 --> 00:18:21.578
What do you mean she's gone?

304
00:18:21.602 --> 00:18:23.270
Mary. she's dead.

305
00:18:25.063 --> 00:18:26.791
What do you mean she's gone?

306
00:18:26.815 --> 00:18:27.816
What do you mean?

307
00:18:30.736 --> 00:18:32.946
When you saw her body. what was it…

308
00:18:35.782 --> 00:18:37.117
What did they do to her?

309
00:18:38.327 --> 00:18:41.038
The wound is on the back of her head.

310
00:18:42.664 --> 00:18:45.375
So her face was still perfect.

311
00:18:51.089 --> 00:18:53.735
What the fuck was
she doing in the arroyo?

312
00:18:53.759 --> 00:18:56.821
I don't know for sure. But…

313
00:18:56.845 --> 00:18:59.640
What do you mean for sure?
Do you know anything else?

314
00:19:01.517 --> 00:19:02.976
She was meeting someone.

315
00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:05.830
What? What do you mean
she was meeting someone?

316
00:19:05.854 --> 00:19:08.291
A guy. Somebody that she was seeing.

317
00:19:08.315 --> 00:19:09.399
My god.

318
00:19:11.485 --> 00:19:13.028
My god.

319
00:19:15.739 --> 00:19:17.926
Is this what you two were
talking about last night

320
00:19:17.950 --> 00:19:19.636
when I came back from the bathroom?

321
00:19:19.660 --> 00:19:22.079
Yes. But. Mary. she didn't…

322
00:19:22.704 --> 00:19:24.557
She barely told me anything.

323
00:19:24.581 --> 00:19:25.582
But you knew.

324
00:19:27.543 --> 00:19:29.521
- Who was he?
- I don't know.

325
00:19:29.545 --> 00:19:32.357
I don't know much. I just
know that he was texting her

326
00:19:32.381 --> 00:19:33.441
and she was upset

327
00:19:33.465 --> 00:19:36.903
and so they must have
still been seeing each other.

328
00:19:36.927 --> 00:19:37.987
- And...
- still?

329
00:19:38.011 --> 00:19:39.572
- Yes.
- Still seeing each other?

330
00:19:39.596 --> 00:19:40.597
Yes.

331
00:19:41.682 --> 00:19:43.267
How long have you known about this?

332
00:19:44.977 --> 00:19:47.163
I don't know. Maybe a couple of weeks.

333
00:19:47.187 --> 00:19:48.873
My god. Jesus. Ellie.

334
00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:51.668
It wasn't my business to tell you.

335
00:19:51.692 --> 00:19:53.002
And I thought that she was gonna end it.

336
00:19:53.026 --> 00:19:54.754
I did not think it was gonna be a big deal.

337
00:19:54.778 --> 00:19:56.154
I did not think that she...

338
00:19:58.907 --> 00:20:00.409
okay. Okay.

339
00:20:02.828 --> 00:20:05.306
Did she tell you anything else about him?

340
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:09.042
She told me that his name is
David. and that they met at work.

341
00:20:10.711 --> 00:20:11.980
Did you tell the police?

342
00:20:12.004 --> 00:20:14.065
Yes. of course. I told them everything.

343
00:20:14.089 --> 00:20:16.925
Well. yeah. but neither
of you told me. so…

344
00:20:18.385 --> 00:20:20.947
What. did you think I
was gonna be judgmental?

345
00:20:20.971 --> 00:20:22.949
- Is that what she thought? That i...
- no. Mary.

346
00:20:22.973 --> 00:20:24.033
I think she…

347
00:20:24.057 --> 00:20:27.078
You know. you can be more
judgmental than me sometimes.

348
00:20:27.102 --> 00:20:28.371
- Okay.
- You know?

349
00:20:28.395 --> 00:20:29.539
Yes. fine.

350
00:20:29.563 --> 00:20:31.374
Maybe that's why she told me. Mary.

351
00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:34.377
because she knew that I would
be harder on her. and I was.

352
00:20:34.401 --> 00:20:37.005
I am the one who told her that
she had to break it off with him.

353
00:20:37.029 --> 00:20:39.924
and so she went to see
him. and now she's dead.

354
00:20:39.948 --> 00:20:41.759
Are you blaming yourself?

355
00:20:41.783 --> 00:20:43.636
You cannot do that.

356
00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:44.745
What happened?

357
00:20:45.829 --> 00:20:47.223
Hey. Marcus.

358
00:20:47.247 --> 00:20:48.474
- Hi. sweetheart.
- Hey.

359
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:50.518
How was it with your
caseworker this morning?

360
00:20:50.542 --> 00:20:52.312
Mom. I'm an actual person now.

361
00:20:52.336 --> 00:20:53.670
You can talk to me.

362
00:20:55.714 --> 00:20:57.049
What… what's going on?

363
00:21:03.847 --> 00:21:05.182
Okay.

364
00:21:07.434 --> 00:21:08.435
Your…

365
00:21:09.770 --> 00:21:13.065
Your aunt Nancy was killed last night.

366
00:21:14.233 --> 00:21:15.835
They found her body.

367
00:21:15.859 --> 00:21:16.961
- My god.
- I'm sorry.

368
00:21:16.985 --> 00:21:19.672
Mom. Come here.

369
00:21:19.696 --> 00:21:21.925
My god. Mom. I'm so sorry.

370
00:21:21.949 --> 00:21:25.136
It's okay. sweetie.

371
00:21:25.160 --> 00:21:27.663
It's okay. I'm sorry.

372
00:21:30.874 --> 00:21:32.435
Okay. sweetheart. Okay.

373
00:21:32.459 --> 00:21:34.211
I'm okay.

374
00:22:32.936 --> 00:22:36.541
Police say there were signs
of a brutal physical assault.

375
00:22:36.565 --> 00:22:39.502
There is no suspect
in custody at this time.

376
00:22:39.526 --> 00:22:41.629
The victim's husband
is Robert hennessey.

377
00:22:41.653 --> 00:22:44.215
whose father is the
founder of hedgerow capital.

378
00:22:44.239 --> 00:22:46.593
Tributes poured in today on social media

379
00:22:46.617 --> 00:22:49.179
where Mrs. Hennessey
amassed thousands of followers.

380
00:22:49.203 --> 00:22:51.496
Do they really think this will help?

381
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:53.498
It might.

382
00:22:54.166 --> 00:22:56.084
Might make people care about her.

383
00:22:56.710 --> 00:22:57.896
Come on.

384
00:22:57.920 --> 00:23:02.609
Be honest. if all you saw was
this highlight reel of her life.

385
00:23:02.633 --> 00:23:04.360
don't you think you would hate her?

386
00:23:04.384 --> 00:23:06.428
Well. hate's an ugly word.

387
00:23:10.182 --> 00:23:12.935
Envy. maybe. If that's all I saw.

388
00:23:13.769 --> 00:23:15.479
This wasn't even the real her.

389
00:23:16.855 --> 00:23:18.458
Yeah. it was. Ellie.

390
00:23:18.482 --> 00:23:19.858
Just wasn't the whole her.

391
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:28.450
Have you seen Cora?

392
00:23:29.117 --> 00:23:31.578
No. Not yet.

393
00:23:55.018 --> 00:23:57.872
I didn't even know my mom
owned any black clothes.

394
00:23:57.896 --> 00:24:02.168
She used to have this
gorgeous black leather jumpsuit

395
00:24:02.192 --> 00:24:04.796
that she wore when we went to the club.

396
00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:06.840
I can't picture that at all.

397
00:24:06.864 --> 00:24:09.300
She always wanted to take me shopping.

398
00:24:09.324 --> 00:24:10.492
I never let her.

399
00:24:11.201 --> 00:24:12.202
I get that.

400
00:24:12.786 --> 00:24:15.974
Mothers and daughters.
it's very complicated.

401
00:24:15.998 --> 00:24:19.227
No. but I would roast her
for all the shopping she did.

402
00:24:19.251 --> 00:24:22.814
Now I'm. like. digging
through her clothes.

403
00:24:22.838 --> 00:24:25.215
trying to find something
to wear to her funeral.

404
00:24:25.841 --> 00:24:26.842
Cora…

405
00:24:28.177 --> 00:24:33.015
If this feels like too much. we
don't have to do this right now.

406
00:24:33.891 --> 00:24:36.226
I can't feel anything. Ellie.

407
00:24:37.186 --> 00:24:39.313
I think you might be in shock.

408
00:24:39.855 --> 00:24:42.792
Is that what it is? 'Cause I feel
like something's wrong with me.

409
00:24:42.816 --> 00:24:45.277
Nothing is wrong with you. okay?

410
00:24:47.446 --> 00:24:52.618
I remember being in this room with
your mom when you were just an infant.

411
00:24:53.493 --> 00:24:59.625
And she was holding you in her
arms. and she was so in love with you.

412
00:25:00.959 --> 00:25:04.505
Nothing made her happier
than being your mom.

413
00:25:05.881 --> 00:25:08.634
And all I did was push her away.

414
00:25:09.426 --> 00:25:11.803
And it's too late now.

415
00:25:14.306 --> 00:25:17.160
Sweetie. it's okay.

416
00:25:17.184 --> 00:25:18.769
I'm here.

417
00:25:22.731 --> 00:25:24.441
Would you stay with us?

418
00:25:25.692 --> 00:25:26.693
Really?

419
00:25:27.277 --> 00:25:29.196
I don't wanna be alone with my dad.

420
00:25:31.490 --> 00:25:32.491
Cora. I…

421
00:25:33.867 --> 00:25:34.928
Okay.

422
00:25:34.952 --> 00:25:38.973
I know that he struggles
with his emotions.

423
00:25:38.997 --> 00:25:42.560
but trust me. I have known him
since I was barely older than you...

424
00:25:42.584 --> 00:25:44.127
it's not just the emotions.

425
00:25:45.379 --> 00:25:47.297
I don't feel safe with him right now.

426
00:25:54.972 --> 00:25:57.242
Look. I don't need a publicist.

427
00:25:57.266 --> 00:25:59.810
I need them to find
out who killed my wife.

428
00:26:01.144 --> 00:26:03.355
It's a crisis firm. Robert.

429
00:26:04.273 --> 00:26:07.293
And daddy just wants
to make the introduction.

430
00:26:07.317 --> 00:26:08.711
That's it.

431
00:26:08.735 --> 00:26:10.320
Ultimately. it's your choice.

432
00:26:11.488 --> 00:26:15.301
Have you given any more
thought to the idea of a reward?

433
00:26:15.325 --> 00:26:18.179
I hate the… I hate the
idea of a bounty hunt.

434
00:26:18.203 --> 00:26:20.306
I know. and no one wants
to put any pressure on you.

435
00:26:20.330 --> 00:26:23.142
but at this point. it's just
about controlling the narrative.

436
00:26:23.166 --> 00:26:24.626
- Hey.
- I mean. we're in...

437
00:26:25.752 --> 00:26:28.106
Eleanor. Didn't know you were here.

438
00:26:28.130 --> 00:26:29.232
Sorry to interrupt.

439
00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:30.608
No. come on in.

440
00:26:30.632 --> 00:26:32.944
Come on in. You've
been such a good friend

441
00:26:32.968 --> 00:26:36.847
to be here with the family for this long.

442
00:26:39.057 --> 00:26:40.934
I was just headed to the kitchen.

443
00:26:41.560 --> 00:26:43.187
Does anyone else need a drink?

444
00:26:43.854 --> 00:26:45.230
No. thank you.

445
00:26:49.318 --> 00:26:51.129
Is it cold in here?

446
00:26:51.153 --> 00:26:53.173
My sister is just trying to help

447
00:26:53.197 --> 00:26:55.175
finish all the alcohol in the house.

448
00:26:55.199 --> 00:26:57.326
Yes. I think she's doing that.

449
00:26:59.745 --> 00:27:03.248
Cora asked me if I would
stay with you guys for a while.

450
00:27:04.082 --> 00:27:07.562
Okay. So. how do you feel about that?

451
00:27:07.586 --> 00:27:09.379
It's not about how I feel.

452
00:27:10.297 --> 00:27:13.175
It's about figuring out
what's best for Cora.

453
00:27:14.134 --> 00:27:16.863
If I haven't thanked you for
everything that you're doing...

454
00:27:16.887 --> 00:27:19.073
don't do that. please. Robert.

455
00:27:19.097 --> 00:27:21.951
No. it's something I forget to do.

456
00:27:21.975 --> 00:27:24.370
I can be a real asshole
like that sometimes.

457
00:27:24.394 --> 00:27:26.480
just taking everyone
around me for granted.

458
00:27:28.065 --> 00:27:29.983
How did Cora seem to you?

459
00:27:33.487 --> 00:27:34.964
Is she scared of me?

460
00:27:34.988 --> 00:27:38.450
She didn't use the word "scared" exactly.

461
00:27:39.576 --> 00:27:44.849
It… it can't be easy losing her mother

462
00:27:44.873 --> 00:27:47.560
and seeing them treat me like a suspect.

463
00:27:47.584 --> 00:27:49.896
They're not calling
you a suspect. are they?

464
00:27:49.920 --> 00:27:51.105
That's where this is headed.

465
00:27:51.129 --> 00:27:52.982
You know. I have no alibi.

466
00:27:53.006 --> 00:27:55.217
I was home alone that
night until I spoke to you.

467
00:27:55.843 --> 00:27:56.903
Sorry.

468
00:27:56.927 --> 00:27:58.178
I can understand

469
00:27:58.762 --> 00:28:03.183
having you around might make her
a little more comfortable right now.

470
00:28:05.060 --> 00:28:07.437
I'm gonna come by as often as I can.

471
00:28:08.063 --> 00:28:11.668
But I… I don't think it's a
good idea for me to stay here.

472
00:28:11.692 --> 00:28:12.752
Yeah.

473
00:28:12.776 --> 00:28:13.878
Okay.

474
00:28:13.902 --> 00:28:15.654
- Okay.
- Thank you.

475
00:28:25.956 --> 00:28:28.309
- Good afternoon.
- Hey. Ms. Bouchet.

476
00:28:28.333 --> 00:28:30.478
Sam. you changed your hair.

477
00:28:30.502 --> 00:28:31.712
- I like it.
- Thanks.

478
00:28:32.629 --> 00:28:33.690
- Hey.
- Hi.

479
00:28:33.714 --> 00:28:36.568
We didn't think you'd be coming in
yet. We would've gotten more prepared.

480
00:28:36.592 --> 00:28:38.778
I'm just coming in to grab a few things.

481
00:28:38.802 --> 00:28:40.488
I didn't wanna disrupt the flow.

482
00:28:40.512 --> 00:28:43.074
No. hey. you're the boss.
You can do whatever you want.

483
00:28:43.098 --> 00:28:44.993
I just thought you'd
want some more time...

484
00:28:45.017 --> 00:28:47.217
I don't wanna make a big
deal of it here at the office.

485
00:28:47.519 --> 00:28:50.540
I am so deeply. deeply
sorry for your loss.

486
00:28:50.564 --> 00:28:52.417
- I can't even imagine.
- Thank you.

487
00:28:52.441 --> 00:28:53.585
There are no words.

488
00:28:53.609 --> 00:28:55.170
No words.

489
00:28:55.194 --> 00:28:56.486
You've said it. Olivia.

490
00:28:59.031 --> 00:29:00.532
Thank you for that.

491
00:29:02.993 --> 00:29:05.054
Some detectives were here earlier.

492
00:29:05.078 --> 00:29:07.831
asking a few questions
about the timing of that night.

493
00:29:08.665 --> 00:29:11.418
I told them I was already gone
by then. so I couldn't help them.

494
00:29:12.169 --> 00:29:15.631
Yeah. they're just ticking boxes.
Trying to establish their timeline.

495
00:29:16.215 --> 00:29:17.275
Right.

496
00:29:17.299 --> 00:29:19.277
We will have to postpone
the middle east trip though.

497
00:29:19.301 --> 00:29:20.361
God. of course.

498
00:29:20.385 --> 00:29:22.947
There's too much going on right
now for you to worry about that.

499
00:29:22.971 --> 00:29:24.723
They don't want me to leave town.

500
00:29:29.019 --> 00:29:32.064
If there's anything I need to
know. you would tell me. right?

501
00:29:34.191 --> 00:29:35.192
Yes.

502
00:29:43.784 --> 00:29:44.952
Hey.

503
00:29:45.994 --> 00:29:48.264
- Hey.
- I've been trying to reach you.

504
00:29:48.288 --> 00:29:50.249
Yeah. it's not a great time.

505
00:29:52.501 --> 00:29:53.561
Are you goin' somewhere?

506
00:29:53.585 --> 00:29:55.796
You're not. like. leaving. right?

507
00:29:56.380 --> 00:29:59.609
No. I'm just grabbing stuff in
case I have to work from home.

508
00:29:59.633 --> 00:30:01.927
I might… maybe going
to my friend's to help.

509
00:30:02.678 --> 00:30:04.221
Who's helping you?

510
00:30:05.097 --> 00:30:07.391
- What?
- I said. who's helping you?

511
00:30:10.435 --> 00:30:11.728
This is your loss too.

512
00:30:14.189 --> 00:30:15.250
Okay.

513
00:30:15.274 --> 00:30:20.529
Jordan. I think what would be most
helpful right now is your discretion.

514
00:30:23.198 --> 00:30:25.009
- Okay?
- Yeah. sure.

515
00:30:25.033 --> 00:30:26.243
Okay. thank you.

516
00:31:25.511 --> 00:31:26.654
Man.

517
00:31:26.678 --> 00:31:27.804
Mare.

518
00:31:29.014 --> 00:31:31.242
- Are you smoking again?
- No.

519
00:31:31.266 --> 00:31:32.410
Yes.

520
00:31:32.434 --> 00:31:34.561
It's not a cigarette.
it's an emotional crutch.

521
00:31:36.897 --> 00:31:40.293
I don't understand why we had
to have this memorial so quickly.

522
00:31:40.317 --> 00:31:42.694
Because Robert wanted
to get it over with. I think.

523
00:31:43.695 --> 00:31:45.215
Shit. shit. shit. Here they come.

524
00:31:45.239 --> 00:31:46.424
Will you just hold this for me?

525
00:31:46.448 --> 00:31:48.218
- What?
- Please. please. Hold it. hold it.

526
00:31:48.242 --> 00:31:49.552
Mary.

527
00:31:49.576 --> 00:31:50.637
Hey. guys.

528
00:31:50.661 --> 00:31:52.871
Aunt Ellie. you're smoking?

529
00:31:54.373 --> 00:31:57.644
It's a… it's a bad habit. but it
doesn't make her a bad person.

530
00:31:57.668 --> 00:31:59.336
Thank you. Howard.

531
00:31:59.837 --> 00:32:01.606
We'll… we'll save two seats for you.

532
00:32:01.630 --> 00:32:02.923
Thank you.

533
00:32:07.928 --> 00:32:09.239
Now they think I smoke.

534
00:32:09.263 --> 00:32:11.866
I'm sorry. but I don't think
we should have brought them.

535
00:32:11.890 --> 00:32:14.160
Howard said we shouldn't
"shield them from grief."

536
00:32:14.184 --> 00:32:17.521
Well. Robert's family planned this.
so there's not gonna be a lot of grief.

537
00:32:18.105 --> 00:32:20.816
We'll get elegance and wasp-y denial.

538
00:32:35.205 --> 00:32:37.433
When does the bride come out?

539
00:32:37.457 --> 00:32:39.394
It's not a wedding. It's a funeral.

540
00:32:39.418 --> 00:32:42.462
Actually. it's a memorial
'cause there's no body.

541
00:32:43.672 --> 00:32:45.984
We don't believe in
shielding them from grief.

542
00:32:46.008 --> 00:32:47.593
Yes. I heard.

543
00:32:50.137 --> 00:32:52.431
Am I crazy or does this
smell like something?

544
00:32:53.891 --> 00:32:54.892
It's Rose pulp.

545
00:32:55.684 --> 00:33:00.165
We had the paper made from linen
and Rose petals from Nancy's garden.

546
00:33:00.189 --> 00:33:02.375
That's… that's so lovely.

547
00:33:02.399 --> 00:33:05.068
You just smashed up her roses and…

548
00:33:05.569 --> 00:33:07.571
Yes. Of course.

549
00:33:08.197 --> 00:33:09.799
You are so kind to come.

550
00:33:09.823 --> 00:33:12.010
- No. please.
- Of course. Mr. Hennessey.

551
00:33:12.034 --> 00:33:13.928
And such beautiful little girls.

552
00:33:13.952 --> 00:33:15.430
Thank you.

553
00:33:15.454 --> 00:33:18.624
I'm so sorry you couldn't find
childcare on such short notice.

554
00:33:19.458 --> 00:33:20.584
Thank you.

555
00:33:47.819 --> 00:33:48.820
El.

556
00:33:50.697 --> 00:33:52.967
El. You're up.

557
00:33:52.991 --> 00:33:53.992
God.

558
00:34:26.525 --> 00:34:31.588
"She walks in beauty. like the night

559
00:34:31.612 --> 00:34:34.533
of cloudless climes and starry skies

560
00:34:35.284 --> 00:34:37.971
and all that's best of dark and bright

561
00:34:37.995 --> 00:34:41.623
meet in her aspect and her eyes

562
00:34:43.041 --> 00:34:45.878
thus mellowed to that tender light

563
00:34:49.255 --> 00:34:52.134
which heaven to gaudy day denies

564
00:34:53.760 --> 00:34:58.432
one shade the more. one ray the less…

565
00:35:07.733 --> 00:35:10.461
It was lovely. don't get
me wrong. It just wasn't…

566
00:35:10.485 --> 00:35:11.838
- Her.
- Yeah.

567
00:35:11.862 --> 00:35:13.089
Yeah.

568
00:35:13.113 --> 00:35:15.508
Well. kit runs a tight ship.

569
00:35:15.532 --> 00:35:19.369
You know she made me send
her that Byron poem for approval?

570
00:35:20.078 --> 00:35:22.515
And then she told me.
"no jokes. no tears."

571
00:35:22.539 --> 00:35:23.916
- Jesus.
- Yeah.

572
00:35:24.541 --> 00:35:28.921
Did you see that guy in the denim
jacket at the church yesterday?

573
00:35:30.339 --> 00:35:32.132
No. I don't think I saw him. Why?

574
00:35:34.760 --> 00:35:37.596
You don't think anybody from
Nancy's family would've come. right?

575
00:35:38.764 --> 00:35:41.725
No. Ellie. they wouldn't have dared.

576
00:35:42.809 --> 00:35:43.810
Right.

577
00:35:45.896 --> 00:35:47.022
Hey. so…

578
00:35:48.440 --> 00:35:50.376
Well. Howard had this thought.

579
00:35:50.400 --> 00:35:53.421
- it was a favor really. to ask.
- Okay.

580
00:35:53.445 --> 00:35:58.218
We wanted to know if it was possible
maybe Marcus could volunteer with you?

581
00:35:58.242 --> 00:36:01.846
Because we thought if he saw
some real suffering in the world.

582
00:36:01.870 --> 00:36:04.599
he could maybe get some
perspective and then he would be more...

583
00:36:04.623 --> 00:36:05.934
yes. yes.

584
00:36:05.958 --> 00:36:08.061
I will find something
for him. if he's willing.

585
00:36:08.085 --> 00:36:09.395
Thank you so much. Ellie.

586
00:36:09.419 --> 00:36:11.129
- That is very generous.
- Mary.

587
00:36:12.047 --> 00:36:13.650
They found him.

588
00:36:13.674 --> 00:36:16.694
Breaking footage of davide haji boyette.

589
00:36:16.718 --> 00:36:18.822
also known as d.H. Boyette…

590
00:36:18.846 --> 00:36:20.406
- There he is.
- …Who we can confirm

591
00:36:20.430 --> 00:36:22.742
- has been officially named…
- no fucking way.

592
00:36:22.766 --> 00:36:24.327
- …as a person of interest…
- that's the guy?

593
00:36:24.351 --> 00:36:27.455
- …In the murder of Nancy hennessey.
- Yeah. That's what they're saying.

594
00:36:27.479 --> 00:36:28.581
Do you know him?

595
00:36:28.605 --> 00:36:30.148
How would I know him?

596
00:36:31.942 --> 00:36:33.527
Why did you ask me that?

597
00:36:35.279 --> 00:36:37.423
Sorry. I shouldn't have assumed.

598
00:36:37.447 --> 00:36:39.324
No. I've never met this person.

599
00:36:40.033 --> 00:36:42.804
Mom's listed on his
website as one of his patrons.

600
00:36:42.828 --> 00:36:44.830
You know. she supported artists.

601
00:36:45.789 --> 00:36:47.433
And he is a painter.

602
00:36:47.457 --> 00:36:49.918
D.h. Boyette. also known as davide.

603
00:36:50.627 --> 00:36:52.796
And there's kit. right on cue.

604
00:36:54.298 --> 00:36:55.859
Do you think this is the guy?

605
00:36:55.883 --> 00:36:58.969
I think we need to be very
careful to not rush to judgment.

606
00:36:59.761 --> 00:37:01.638
Let's let them talk to him… my god.

607
00:37:06.143 --> 00:37:07.144
What?

608
00:37:07.936 --> 00:37:09.581
- What?
- My god.

609
00:37:09.605 --> 00:37:10.606
What?

610
00:37:11.190 --> 00:37:12.191
Ellie?

611
00:37:15.652 --> 00:37:17.237
Shit.

612
00:37:18.071 --> 00:37:20.675
"D.h. Boyette." She just
put this one up. didn't she?

613
00:37:20.699 --> 00:37:22.367
Right before she died. That's him.

614
00:37:23.243 --> 00:37:24.578
Is that mom?

615
00:37:30.292 --> 00:37:32.604
- Goddamn.
- Hey. hey. Robert. Robert.

616
00:37:32.628 --> 00:37:33.897
- Dad?
- What are you doing?

617
00:37:33.921 --> 00:37:36.441
- Wh... dad. stop! What are you...
- what are you doing?

618
00:37:36.465 --> 00:37:37.901
- Dad! Ellie!
- Hey!

619
00:37:37.925 --> 00:37:39.009
Stop!

620
00:37:40.177 --> 00:37:41.654
- Robert!
- Dad!

621
00:37:41.678 --> 00:37:43.615
- Do something. Ellie!
- Robert.

622
00:37:43.639 --> 00:37:45.408
- Robert. where are you going?
- Dad. Dad!

623
00:37:45.432 --> 00:37:46.993
- Stop it. What are you doing?
- Stop. dad! Dad!

624
00:37:47.017 --> 00:37:48.077
Stay here. please.

625
00:37:48.101 --> 00:37:49.329
Stop it. Robert. Stop it.

626
00:37:49.353 --> 00:37:51.289
My god. Robert. You have to stop.

627
00:37:51.313 --> 00:37:52.981
You have to take a beat.

628
00:37:53.732 --> 00:37:56.777
Jesus. Robert. What are you doing?

629
00:37:58.278 --> 00:37:59.589
Can we talk about this inside?

630
00:37:59.613 --> 00:38:01.174
I just want you to take a beat.

631
00:38:01.198 --> 00:38:02.491
I want you to take a breath.

632
00:38:05.536 --> 00:38:07.055
My god. Robert. please.

633
00:38:07.079 --> 00:38:09.098
- She never belonged to me.
- Please stop it.

634
00:38:09.122 --> 00:38:12.560
I always wanted her to be
all mine. but she never was.

635
00:38:12.584 --> 00:38:14.813
There was always a piece
of her that wouldn't be.

636
00:38:14.837 --> 00:38:16.314
And I always fucking knew it!

637
00:38:16.338 --> 00:38:18.858
Robert. I think that they
have people watching.

638
00:38:18.882 --> 00:38:20.985
- I don't give a fuck.
- I understand that you're angry.

639
00:38:21.009 --> 00:38:22.237
You need to calm down.

640
00:38:22.261 --> 00:38:23.530
Hey.

641
00:38:23.554 --> 00:38:26.181
Don't tell me how I should feel.

642
00:38:27.307 --> 00:38:28.785
Jesus Christ. Eleanor.

643
00:38:28.809 --> 00:38:30.703
You don't know everything. all right?

644
00:38:30.727 --> 00:38:32.271
She was my fucking wife.

645
00:38:47.661 --> 00:38:49.264
Does he have an alibi?

646
00:38:49.288 --> 00:38:50.473
Davide?

647
00:38:50.497 --> 00:38:52.433
Yeah. the guy she was sleeping with.

648
00:38:52.457 --> 00:38:57.814
Kind of. He was maybe at this art
event of some sort. but he left early.

649
00:38:57.838 --> 00:38:59.649
Honestly. they don't
have a lot of information.

650
00:38:59.673 --> 00:39:01.734
I just… I don't think it's him.

651
00:39:01.758 --> 00:39:04.445
She only told you his first
name. We have nothing to go on.

652
00:39:04.469 --> 00:39:06.489
It could absolutely be him.

653
00:39:06.513 --> 00:39:08.533
She would have told me if he was black.

654
00:39:08.557 --> 00:39:10.243
She hardly told you anything about him.

655
00:39:10.267 --> 00:39:12.662
But I am her best and only black friend.

656
00:39:12.686 --> 00:39:14.205
This would have come up.

657
00:39:14.229 --> 00:39:15.230
Okay.

658
00:39:19.943 --> 00:39:21.921
I gave the police the name David.

659
00:39:21.945 --> 00:39:23.673
What if it's not this davide person?

660
00:39:23.697 --> 00:39:26.116
Then we still don't know
who killed our best friend.

661
00:39:29.578 --> 00:39:31.598
I've never seen Robert that angry.

662
00:39:31.622 --> 00:39:35.792
He… he has a temper.
especially when he drinks…

663
00:39:37.794 --> 00:39:39.129
Or when he's jealous.

664
00:39:39.796 --> 00:39:43.735
No. he… you know he loved
her more than anything.

665
00:39:43.759 --> 00:39:46.237
Anger isn't the opposite of love.

666
00:39:46.261 --> 00:39:48.597
Sometimes it's the truest expression of it.

667
00:39:49.932 --> 00:39:54.895
You can't see it because
Robert is your… my what?

668
00:39:55.479 --> 00:39:57.248
My friend? He's your friend.

669
00:39:57.272 --> 00:40:01.693
You and Robert have a connection.

670
00:40:02.194 --> 00:40:03.796
Yes. her name is Nancy.

671
00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:05.280
Outside of Nancy.

672
00:40:06.323 --> 00:40:07.741
And Nancy knew it too.

673
00:40:10.494 --> 00:40:11.787
What are you saying?

674
00:40:14.164 --> 00:40:16.583
You're not the only
person she confided in.

675
00:40:19.628 --> 00:40:20.879
That's all.

676
00:40:39.773 --> 00:40:41.275
- God!
- Sorry.

677
00:40:42.150 --> 00:40:43.350
I didn't mean to frighten you.

678
00:40:43.986 --> 00:40:45.213
How did you get in here?

679
00:40:45.237 --> 00:40:47.382
Someone propped up the door.

680
00:40:47.406 --> 00:40:48.550
I should… should've texted.

681
00:40:48.574 --> 00:40:49.575
Yes.

682
00:40:50.701 --> 00:40:52.411
So can we…

683
00:41:09.636 --> 00:41:11.138
Look. I…

684
00:41:14.349 --> 00:41:15.976
I owe you an apology.

685
00:41:16.643 --> 00:41:20.522
The way that I was behaving.
and what I said was cruel.

686
00:41:22.316 --> 00:41:25.235
She was my wife. but…

687
00:41:26.737 --> 00:41:28.989
I know you guys were
everything to each other.

688
00:41:31.283 --> 00:41:32.284
I'm sorry.

689
00:41:35.746 --> 00:41:36.788
Thank you.

690
00:41:40.792 --> 00:41:44.046
I don't think I realized how much
I needed to hear that from you.

691
00:41:45.255 --> 00:41:47.591
Are you gonna tell me
why you're so dressed up?

692
00:41:48.842 --> 00:41:50.445
This is dressed up to you?

693
00:41:50.469 --> 00:41:52.387
This is how I leave the
house after sundown.

694
00:41:55.182 --> 00:41:56.850
Where are you going?

695
00:41:57.434 --> 00:42:02.957
You know how Nancy loves…
well. loved. the ballet. and how I...

696
00:42:02.981 --> 00:42:04.334
don't. You hate it.

697
00:42:04.358 --> 00:42:06.336
- I don't hate it. I just… I find it…
- you do.

698
00:42:06.360 --> 00:42:08.338
What's that French expression?

699
00:42:08.362 --> 00:42:11.758
- It's fucking boring.
- That's not French.

700
00:42:11.782 --> 00:42:13.676
My legs don't fit in the seats.

701
00:42:13.700 --> 00:42:14.701
What?

702
00:42:17.829 --> 00:42:20.415
Anyways. We're supposed
to go to the opening tonight.

703
00:42:21.959 --> 00:42:22.960
And…

704
00:42:23.836 --> 00:42:25.980
Well. I don't know what to
do. I'm… I'm just banging around

705
00:42:26.004 --> 00:42:27.649
in that big empty house. alone.

706
00:42:27.673 --> 00:42:28.900
I can't sleep.

707
00:42:28.924 --> 00:42:33.971
I'm just walking around looking
for her. but she's not there.

708
00:42:35.222 --> 00:42:36.682
So I was thinking that m…

709
00:42:37.349 --> 00:42:39.953
I don't know. Maybe
at the ballet. I could...

710
00:42:39.977 --> 00:42:42.872
you could feel her with you.

711
00:42:42.896 --> 00:42:43.897
Yeah.

712
00:42:47.276 --> 00:42:48.277
Yeah.

713
00:42:48.777 --> 00:42:51.989
Exactly. Do you think that's possible?

714
00:42:52.489 --> 00:42:56.827
I don't know what's possible anymore.

715
00:42:58.036 --> 00:42:59.246
Okay.

716
00:42:59.746 --> 00:43:00.914
She was just here.

717
00:43:02.833 --> 00:43:08.148
You know. we were all just here
playing stupid fucking card games.

718
00:43:08.172 --> 00:43:10.733
And now she's just gone forever.

719
00:43:10.757 --> 00:43:12.593
It's like I can't…

720
00:43:14.219 --> 00:43:16.013
It doesn't make any sense.

721
00:43:16.513 --> 00:43:20.326
So why shouldn't I be able to go
to a place that she loved so much.

722
00:43:20.350 --> 00:43:22.144
and… and feel her?

723
00:43:24.605 --> 00:43:26.148
I think you have to try.

724
00:43:28.358 --> 00:43:31.695
But will… will you try with me?

725
00:43:35.324 --> 00:43:37.034
You want me to go?

726
00:43:38.035 --> 00:43:40.180
- Yeah.
- No.

727
00:43:40.204 --> 00:43:41.371
What? Why not?

728
00:43:43.123 --> 00:43:45.518
I can't… I just can't.

729
00:43:45.542 --> 00:43:46.853
I mean. the optics.

730
00:43:46.877 --> 00:43:48.313
Fuck the optics.

731
00:43:48.337 --> 00:43:49.689
Who cares about the optics?

732
00:43:49.713 --> 00:43:51.256
I do. You should.

733
00:43:51.798 --> 00:43:55.945
We can't just get dressed up and
have a night out on the town together.

734
00:43:55.969 --> 00:43:57.262
No. I'm… I'm sorry.

735
00:43:59.848 --> 00:44:00.849
I'm sorry.

736
00:44:02.017 --> 00:44:03.018
It was…

737
00:44:03.602 --> 00:44:04.853
It was a stupid idea.

738
00:44:05.687 --> 00:44:06.688
I'm sorry.

739
00:45:17.259 --> 00:45:20.387
My mother has this
expression she loves.

740
00:45:21.930 --> 00:45:27.102
"Have more than you show.
say less than you know."

741
00:45:27.895 --> 00:45:31.124
It was advice I took to heart.

742
00:45:31.148 --> 00:45:36.236
guarding not only what
we had. but how I felt.

743
00:45:36.945 --> 00:45:41.992
Sometimes I hid it so well. I
couldn't even see it myself.

744
00:45:49.958 --> 00:45:51.084
Ms. Bouchet.

745
00:45:52.586 --> 00:45:54.689
I thought you were
worried about the optics?

746
00:45:54.713 --> 00:45:55.714
I was.

747
00:45:56.924 --> 00:46:00.594
But then I remembered that
French expression. "fuck the optics."

748
00:46:02.221 --> 00:46:03.222
Right.

749
00:46:04.014 --> 00:46:05.307
Shall we?

750
00:46:31.041 --> 00:46:36.713
I hope this isn't inappropriate. but
the boss's daughter cleans up real nice.

751
00:46:38.006 --> 00:46:40.634
Just try to get me a
usable shot this time. okay?

751
